main event: An indirect report of a metallic dumbbell-shaped object observed in Kane, Pennsylvania on July 25, 1953.
interesting points: The object had 3 blue lights on each end and 3 lights on the front., It exhibited very fast, rapid zig-zag movements up and down the horizon., The observer used binoculars for a clearer view of the object., The observer appeared to be highly excited or anxious during the sighting., Following-up reports indicated that there could be five other unnamed observers at the same location.
sighted object: metallic dumbbell-shaped object with blue lights
witness description: information furnished by civilians; the observer did not actually see the object but received information from the two observers listed.
